   <text:h text:outline-level="2">
    Clinical Summary
   </text:h>

   <text:p>
    This is an example of a clinical document.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    Bart Davidson attended clinic today for a routine follow-up review.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    Mood appeared stable and no acute distress was observed.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    The patient denied suicidal ideation or recent self-harm.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    Sleep pattern described as variable with intermittent insomnia.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    Appetite reported as normal.
   </text:p>

   <text:p>
    No visual or auditory hallucinations reported during assessment.
   </text:p>

   <text:h text:outline-level="2">
    Medication
   </text:h>

   <text:p>
    He is on
    <text:span text:style-name="MedicationDose">100mg</text:span>
    <text:span text:style-name="MedicationName">Paracetamol</text:span>,
    and
    <text:span text:style-name="MedicationDose">20 milligrams</text:span>
    <text:span text:style-name="MedicationName">clozapine</text:span>.
   </text:p>

   <table:table table:name="MedicationTable">

    <table:table-row>
      <table:table-cell office:value-type="string">
        <text:p>Medication</text:p>
      </table:table-cell>

      <table:table-cell office:value-type="string">
